00:55:13.646 --> 00:55:15.160
Believing for supernatural encounters.

00:55:15.160 --> 00:55:26.540
But I was talking about what I said prophetically today about the anointing increasing and the anointing to increase was coming in a greater capacity, and that word was amazing.

00:55:26.540 --> 00:55:32.520
I'll have to share it again tomorrow because I don't remember all of it.

00:55:32.520 --> 00:55:34.970
Some of it was private.

00:55:34.970 --> 00:55:41.785
That's why I didn't want you to share the wrong thing.

00:55:41.785 --> 00:55:43.110
But it was beautiful.

00:55:43.857 --> 00:55:45.160
And my scribe over there, he knows.

00:55:45.160 --> 00:55:51.509
I know he knows, but he doesn't know what he can share and what he can't.

00:55:51.509 --> 00:55:56.600
But Holy Spirit, what was that that was so beautiful?

00:55:56.600 --> 00:55:57.533
Oh, I remember.

00:55:57.533 --> 00:56:03.570
The Holy Spirit just told me there's so many that believe that the gifts...

00:56:03.570 --> 00:56:04.310
He said, 'I'm...

00:56:16.909 --> 00:56:17.303
you're not...

00:56:17.303 --> 00:56:18.880
I'm not required.

00:56:19.273 --> 00:56:21.514
You feel like you're entitled.

00:56:21.514 --> 00:56:22.337
' Entitled.

00:56:32.080 --> 00:56:32.440
A lot of people walk with this entitlement.

00:56:42.547 --> 00:56:43.320
You think that you don't have to die to self.

00:56:55.631 --> 00:56:55.840
He was talking about it being owed: 'The blessings are owed to me.

00:56:55.840 --> 00:56:58.485
' And He was talking about the attitude of the believer.

00:57:16.600 --> 00:57:17.808
He said, 'You think it's earned?

00:57:17.808 --> 00:57:22.571
' He said, 'It's by My grace.

00:57:22.571 --> 00:57:24.240
' But Brandon, it is qualified.

00:57:24.240 --> 00:57:26.415
You qualify for this level of the glory.

00:57:26.415 --> 00:57:27.856
You qualify by the refining fire.

00:57:28.072 --> 00:57:34.873
And He was talking about the qualifications of the refining fire, that it's not owed to you.

00:57:34.873 --> 00:57:41.260
You qualify when you go into the glorious outpouring.

00:57:41.730 --> 00:57:49.800
And He was talking about certain people walking in it and you have this attitude that you don't have to live a holy, separated life unto Him.

00:57:50.320 --> 00:57:51.186
And so it was beautiful.

00:57:51.186 --> 00:57:59.587
I don't want to butcher it; I'll save it for another day.

00:57:59.587 --> 00:58:05.000
But I remember some of it, and I was sitting there going...

00:58:05.000 --> 00:58:08.120
we had a time with the Lord today.

00:58:08.120 --> 00:58:15.800
Paisley goes, 'I just love it when Jesus visits like that and He talks.

00:58:15.800 --> 00:58:21.629
' She goes, 'Oh, I just love it when Jesus talks like that.

00:58:21.629 --> 00:58:23.989
' It was really beautiful, wasn't it?

00:58:23.989 --> 00:58:27.560
Because we had this time with the Lord.

00:58:27.560 --> 00:58:32.535
But I'll go through it and really get it good so I don't deliver and mess it up for y'all.

00:58:32.535 --> 00:58:43.017
But it was the way He was talking about the greater glory and how you go from glory to glory and you accelerate, you acclimate.

00:58:52.773 --> 00:58:53.320
You accelerate, you acclimate.

00:59:08.246 --> 00:59:08.583
And how each level is...

00:59:11.400 --> 00:59:11.690
you pass the test.

00:59:16.240 --> 00:59:26.344
And He said as you go to these higher levels, as you come up higher with Him, what you did at kindergarten or first grade, you can't do in your Master's or your PhD when you're getting a doctorate.

00:59:26.344 --> 00:59:27.820
There's levels of glory.

00:59:27.820 --> 00:59:36.660
There's levels of being with Him that He requires more of you as you come up higher.

00:59:36.660 --> 00:59:39.147
Thank You, Holy Spirit.

00:59:39.147 --> 00:59:41.372
He's given me more.

00:59:42.232 --> 00:59:42.404
I remember.

00:59:42.404 --> 00:59:52.920
So He said to me, as we pray in the spirit, as you pray in tongues, there's levels of praying in tongues and certain syllables.

00:59:52.920 --> 00:59:53.880
There's certain things...

00:59:53.880 --> 00:59:58.463
He said, 'Remember, I taught you all that He leads, we follow.

00:59:58.463 --> 01:00:13.907
' It's like a dance and like a symphony, and as one brings in their harmony with the flute or the trumpet or whatever, it sounds beautiful, but everybody brings their supply.

01:00:13.907 --> 01:00:20.384
But He was teaching me that you can say a lot in tongues.

01:00:22.623 --> 01:00:29.200
You can go on autopilot and you can just be there and talk and talk.

01:00:29.200 --> 01:00:31.870
Then you go, 'Well, what was that all about?

01:00:31.870 --> 01:00:35.573
' But it really wasn't from the innermost being, from your spirit.

01:00:35.573 --> 01:00:40.848
You just are praying from your head in the spirit and it's like autopilot.

01:00:40.848 --> 01:00:52.360
But He said if you're led in prayer by the Spirit of God by repeating syllables and phrases, the prayer...

01:00:52.360 --> 01:01:02.090
He said you can pray 15 minutes in this kind of prayer, and it will be more effective than if you had prayed for hours on autopilot.

01:01:04.229 --> 01:01:05.000
A lot of you know what I'm saying—autopilot—you're not engaged.

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:13.720
You're just letting your mind wander and you're praying throughout the house, which is good.

01:01:13.720 --> 01:01:16.314
I'm glad you do that; it's better than nothing.

01:01:25.080 --> 01:01:34.016
But He said there's a higher level of intercession that you can go and touch things in the spirit realm if you let the Holy Spirit flow through you and how you pray in the spirit and how you yield to Him phrases.

01:01:34.016 --> 01:01:40.730
And He said, 'Sometimes I'll have you repeat that same phrase four or five times because it's effective.

01:01:40.730 --> 01:01:46.120
' Don't be worried about how it sounds.

01:01:46.120 --> 01:01:49.100
It doesn't matter.

01:01:49.100 --> 01:01:52.425
It's flowing with the dance.

01:01:52.425 --> 01:02:06.000
And if you feel a certain tug inside of your spirit when you're praying that certain way, that syllable or whatever you're getting in tongues, keep hitting that until you feel the dance shift.

01:02:08.780 --> 01:02:22.020
And he said that way of prayer is more effective by being led by His Spirit, because He knows not what we should pray, but the Spirit prays through us and for us, which is what the Bible says.

01:02:22.020 --> 01:02:35.583
So when you pray by the Spirit, by the leading of the Holy Spirit—and He's the leader of the dance and you're just following as He is the conductor—it doesn't matter what it sounds like to you.

01:02:35.583 --> 01:02:42.480
It's what the Holy Spirit is praying through you by yielding to the Holy Spirit.

01:02:42.480 --> 01:02:43.800
"Help me to pray.

01:02:54.524 --> 01:02:54.672
I need help.

01:02:59.520 --> 01:02:59.836
I don't want to pray ineffectively.

01:02:59.836 --> 01:03:07.291
" Well, praying in tongues is good, but there's an autopilot tongue.

01:03:07.291 --> 01:03:13.660
The Lord said there are different levels of praying in the Spirit and there are different dimensions.

01:03:13.660 --> 01:03:19.983
There are different rooms, and most of you will not understand this until you mature.

01:03:19.983 --> 01:03:22.791
This is the effective prayer that I'm talking about.

01:03:22.791 --> 01:03:28.240
This is like saying you're not in grade school anymore; you're going to middle school or high school.

01:03:35.080 --> 01:03:35.289
And that's what the Lord said: this is going from glory to glory.

01:03:35.289 --> 01:03:40.280
As you pray this way and you get those cues, you're not leading the prayer.

01:03:40.280 --> 01:03:47.013
You're not just saying, "I'm just praying for my family, my son," and just praying in tongues and letting it go.

01:03:47.013 --> 01:04:02.975
But when you yield to the Spirit of God and let Him pray through you, you'll feel those cues: "Go here, go here.

01:04:02.975 --> 01:04:10.794
" You'll hear it and pray that, and you'll feel that syllable just did something in your spirit because you're being sensitive to the Spirit.

01:04:14.623 --> 01:04:19.960
You can feel the Holy Spirit moving and you'll go, "That was effective.

01:04:24.636 --> 01:04:24.764
" You can feel it, and you just keep hitting it; it's like hitting the target.

01:04:41.234 --> 01:04:41.531
And that's why He said if you can pray 15 minutes that way, it's more effective than praying hours the other way.

01:04:41.531 --> 01:04:44.211
He brought up Rachel Teafatiller.

01:04:44.211 --> 01:04:46.905
He brought up Sister Wilkerson.

01:04:46.905 --> 01:04:49.130
He brought up Sister Lynne Hammond.

01:04:49.130 --> 01:04:52.920
He brought up these people who are effective prayer warriors.

01:04:52.920 --> 01:04:56.503
And He said, "Brandon, they all graduated from this autopilot.

01:04:56.503 --> 01:05:06.600
If you want to come up higher, you must be led by the Spirit, even in praying in the Spirit, and it's more effective.

01:05:11.693 --> 01:05:11.987
A few minutes of this is worth hours of it.

01:05:23.690 --> 01:05:23.955
" And He said, "You'll accomplish much more.

01:05:23.955 --> 01:05:27.774
" But there are deeper, greater rivers of the Spirit other than autopilot tongues.

01:05:27.774 --> 01:05:28.359
Pray effectively.

01:05:41.218 --> 01:05:41.356
That's why He was instructing me today as we were driving around.

01:05:41.356 --> 01:05:47.920
Then He went into talking about the greater glory and what's about to happen with the church and the last outpouring.

01:05:47.920 --> 01:05:51.255
He's teaching me atmospheres, notes, and syllables.

01:05:51.410 --> 01:05:56.509
He said Kim Clement was developed in certain tunes.

01:05:56.509 --> 01:06:10.253
When he hit a certain note on a piano, if you hit it by the Spirit of God, it's the way it flows.

01:06:19.640 --> 01:06:20.080
You flow in the Spirit with it, and the Holy Spirit is leading you.

01:06:22.770 --> 01:06:29.930
You get different levels of the glory through worship that is not earthly worship; it's heavenly worship.

01:06:29.930 --> 01:06:45.680
You're not praying out of your natural mind; you're praying by the Spirit of God and it's flowing out of you.

01:06:45.680 --> 01:06:49.301
Out of you shall flow rivers of living water.

01:06:49.301 --> 01:07:01.486
Let those rivers flow and you'll go into dimensions in the spirit realm that will forever change your life, because there are levels of the Spirit that you know not of.

01:07:05.120 --> 01:07:05.305
I told you that God is endless.

01:07:15.674 --> 01:07:16.063
There is no beginning and there is no end.

01:07:30.954 --> 01:07:31.246
In Him are dimensions.

01:07:31.246 --> 01:07:32.373
He is dimension.

01:07:43.265 --> 01:07:43.530
In the spirit realm, there are dimensions of prayer.

01:07:44.590 --> 01:07:57.490
I can feel it when you enter into that room, when you enter into what I'm trying to tell you by praying into those syllables and those phrases by the Holy Ghost and allowing the Holy Spirit to flow.

01:07:57.490 --> 01:08:04.213
He knows exactly how to pinpoint target prayers concerning your life, and it's more effective than saying, "Well, I'm believing for this.

01:08:04.213 --> 01:08:07.528
" He knows exactly what you need before you need it.

01:08:07.528 --> 01:08:11.540
So I'm just learning, following the cues in songs and certain notes.

01:08:23.480 --> 01:08:23.662
That's what I was talking about to Donna.

01:08:23.662 --> 01:08:29.328
She said, "Daddy would do that a lot; he would make us repeat those same phrases over and over again.

01:08:29.520 --> 01:08:33.823
" It's not chanting like monks do; they try to copycat the authentic with the counterfeit.

01:08:39.680 --> 01:08:39.845
But God's way is so much more beautiful and so much higher.

01:08:39.845 --> 01:08:44.209
His ways are higher than our ways; His thoughts are higher than our thoughts.

01:08:44.209 --> 01:08:50.305
He is a good God and He is merciful, wonderful, and worthy to be praised.

01:08:50.305 --> 01:08:59.799
If we come up higher in these last days with our prayer walk together as a family on this channel, we will be more effective.

01:08:59.799 --> 01:09:04.840
If we learn to pray this way together—how much more would 4,500 of us?

01:09:06.839 --> 01:09:06.990
I think, Braden, 4,500.

01:09:06.990 --> 01:09:21.510
If we could learn all together as a prayer army to pray effectively and let the Holy Spirit lead and learn to flow with the syllables as you feel led, think about what we could get accomplished in the spirit realm.

01:09:21.510 --> 01:09:23.564
There's nothing we can't accomplish with the Holy Spirit working through you.

01:09:23.564 --> 01:09:26.600
We are more than conquerors, but we have been snared by ignorance.

01:09:26.600 --> 01:09:39.400
When we are led by our emotions and not led by the Spirit of God—for those who are led by the Spirit of God are the sons and daughters of God.

01:09:39.400 --> 01:09:48.665
We are led by Him and filled with the Holy Ghost in these last days, and that's what's going to be effective.

01:09:48.665 --> 01:09:54.609
I want pinpoint target prayers, not praying way over here and way over there.

01:09:54.609 --> 01:09:59.070
I want to see the prayer that gets results and changes things.

01:09:59.070 --> 01:10:14.360
That's why I'm trying to bring things like this to you and these little pocketbooks, because don't you get tired of doing the same thing and expecting different results while you're still broke or bound?

01:10:14.360 --> 01:10:20.549
You've got some devil tormenting your marriage, or your kids are strung out.

01:10:20.549 --> 01:10:23.900
Don't you get tired of that?

01:10:23.900 --> 01:10:30.551
That's why I told Donna, "I want prayer that changes things.

01:10:30.551 --> 01:10:32.169
I want to see results.

01:10:40.183 --> 01:10:42.650
" Do you get tired of the world seeming to be at more peace than a lot of Christians?

01:10:42.650 --> 01:10:49.860
I talked to one man who said he doesn't even like to do business with Christians; he'd rather do business with the world.

01:11:02.709 --> 01:11:03.091
I thought, "Why is that?

01:11:03.091 --> 01:11:04.500
" That's not healthy.

01:11:15.090 --> 01:11:15.260
But this was a real, legitimate statement from this man.

01:11:34.500 --> 01:11:34.665
And I looked at him and I went...

01:11:37.097 --> 01:11:37.229
He was sincere.

01:11:37.229 --> 01:11:45.204
He goes, 'Because more than likely Christians will backstab you and run you down, and the world won't.

01:11:45.204 --> 01:11:47.987
I know what to get from them.

01:11:47.987 --> 01:11:51.503
' I looked at him and said, 'I know.

01:11:51.503 --> 01:11:54.149
I've been there concerning certain things and business deals.

01:12:08.480 --> 01:12:08.800
I understand what you're saying, but not us.

01:12:08.800 --> 01:12:11.930
' But not us, right?

01:12:26.800 --> 01:12:27.035
We're the salt.

01:12:27.035 --> 01:12:27.975
We're the light.

01:12:27.975 --> 01:12:30.510
And the world sees it on us.

01:12:30.510 --> 01:12:35.230
And as He is, so are we in this world.

01:12:46.520 --> 01:12:48.735
I say it over myself all the time: that light would shine on our face and the world would say, 'There's something different about them.

01:12:48.735 --> 01:12:52.480
There's something different.

01:12:52.480 --> 01:13:01.480
They have a peace that I'm not familiar with.

01:13:01.480 --> 01:13:09.280
They have a joy that I'm not familiar with.

01:13:09.280 --> 01:13:19.248
They walk in a marriage—their marriage is good.

01:13:19.248 --> 01:13:23.331
Their children are healthy.

01:13:23.331 --> 01:13:33.590
Their children are obedient, and they've got a light on them.

01:13:33.600 --> 01:13:38.510
They're not normal teenagers.

01:13:38.520 --> 01:13:47.211
' I'm not familiar with the level of success.

01:13:47.211 --> 01:14:07.680
I remember what Pastor Chip said about Jack Nicklaus looking at Tiger Woods while he was out there playing golf.

01:14:07.680 --> 01:14:24.120
Pastor Chip said Jack Nicklaus said as they interviewed him, 'What do you think about Tiger Woods?

01:14:24.120 --> 01:14:50.857
' and he said Jack Nicklaus was one of the greatest, and he looked over and said, 'I'm not familiar with the success.

01:14:50.857 --> 01:14:55.780
I've never seen that before.

01:14:55.780 --> 01:15:00.387
I'm not familiar with that.

01:15:00.387 --> 01:15:16.480
I'm not familiar with the level of success that Tiger Woods is operating in right now.

01:15:16.480 --> 01:15:34.480
' Jack Nicklaus said it, and I thought when he said it, it challenged me: why not you?

01:15:34.480 --> 01:15:34.932
Why not me?

01:15:34.932 --> 01:15:36.739
Why not us?

01:15:37.643 --> 01:15:51.183
The world looks and says, 'I'm not familiar with the success that they're walking in.

01:15:51.183 --> 01:15:53.789
' They're blessed.

01:15:53.789 --> 01:15:57.727
There are people who are blessed.

01:15:57.727 --> 01:16:03.920
There are people who walk in blessing.

01:16:03.920 --> 01:16:11.080
There are people who walk in health.

01:16:30.880 --> 01:16:31.373
You know what?

01:16:31.373 --> 01:16:36.966
I've never seen a family get along like that.

01:16:36.966 --> 01:16:56.470
There's peace when I go around them, and you see them in Walmart or whatever; there's just a peace that flows through them.

01:16:56.470 --> 01:17:02.860
I'm really not familiar with that, but I want to know about it.

01:17:35.451 --> 01:17:35.669
I want to know about what's on the inside.

01:17:35.669 --> 01:17:36.810
How do they do that?

01:17:36.810 --> 01:17:40.760
How are they successful?

01:17:40.760 --> 01:17:44.246
How do they always win?

01:17:44.246 --> 01:17:48.024
I want to be a winner.

01:18:01.280 --> 01:18:01.720
I don't want a participation trophy.

01:18:04.360 --> 01:18:04.605
I want the first-place trophy.

01:18:07.740 --> 01:18:12.620
I love that we're in it to win it, to be the head and not the tail, above and not beneath.

01:18:32.760 --> 01:18:33.456
And that's why I think prayer that is effective is a winning prayer.

01:18:33.456 --> 01:18:36.747
It's not a whining prayer.

01:18:36.747 --> 01:18:37.591
You're a believing believer.

01:18:37.591 --> 01:18:45.137
God is able to do through you exceedingly, abundantly, above all that you dare ask or think, according to the power that works in you.

01:18:59.960 --> 01:19:00.258
And you're a believing believer.

01:19:00.258 --> 01:19:01.747
I'm not a doubter.

01:19:01.747 --> 01:19:11.320
I'm a believer, and I'm an overcomer by the blood of the Lamb and by the word of my testimony.

01:19:11.320 --> 01:19:14.000
You either believe it or you don't.

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:15.600
I'm not a victim.

01:19:15.600 --> 01:19:17.000
I'm a victor.

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:19.183
That's what the Lord told me.

01:19:19.183 --> 01:19:23.263
He said, 'Braden, you can't be a victim and go on the glory side and the victory side.

01:19:41.528 --> 01:19:41.732
A victim doesn't walk on the victory side.

01:19:41.732 --> 01:19:43.733
' 'Well, I've had all this.

01:19:43.733 --> 01:19:54.180
' The Lord said, 'Brandon, who hasn't had a story?

01:19:54.180 --> 01:19:56.610
Everybody has a story.

01:19:56.610 --> 01:20:00.040
Everybody's had something hard they've been through in their life.

01:20:00.040 --> 01:20:03.340
You're not anything different.

01:20:03.340 --> 01:21:38.434
Yeah, you have a child that's overcome special needs, and you've got a child that's overcoming autism, and you've got this stuff going on, but there's somebody else with a worse story than you.

01:21:44.204 --> 01:21:50.540
And you can either camp around your sad pity party and how you feel sorry for yourself, but you can look across the street and see somebody that has it a lot worse.

01:21:53.276 --> 01:21:55.510
And there's always somebody that's overcoming something different than you are.

01:21:55.510 --> 01:21:59.000
' But I refuse to be a victim and not a victor.

01:22:00.178 --> 01:22:54.880
The ones that get the job done are the ones that have that bulldog faith and say, 'I refuse.

01:22:54.880 --> 01:23:00.531
' As the Lord was driving around today, He said, 'You've got to practice like a champion.

01:23:00.531 --> 01:23:02.390
You've got to believe.

01:23:02.390 --> 01:23:10.526
' What did Michael Jordan do, in his natural ability, to practice to be a winner?

01:23:10.526 --> 01:23:17.140
You've got to think this is the major leagues.

01:23:17.140 --> 01:23:19.434
That's what He said to me.

01:23:19.434 --> 01:23:22.600
'You've got to think this is the major leagues.

01:23:22.600 --> 01:23:25.240
You can't think in the minor leagues.

01:23:34.926 --> 01:23:35.263
This isn't college level anymore.

01:23:35.263 --> 01:23:38.583
You've got to think and train like a champion.

01:23:38.583 --> 01:23:41.954
' That's what Pastor Chip would even tell us.

01:23:41.954 --> 01:23:47.440
You've got to think and train like a champion.

01:23:47.440 --> 01:23:55.420
You can't be thinking the way you're thinking anymore, worried about whatever.

01:23:55.420 --> 01:24:01.183
What did Michael Jordan do to get where he is?

01:24:01.183 --> 01:24:03.665
What did Derek Jeter do?

01:24:28.880 --> 01:24:29.858
What did John Elway do?

01:24:29.858 --> 01:24:38.653
What did Troy Aikman, Michael Irvin, or Emmitt Smith, the greats, do to get where they were?

01:24:38.653 --> 01:24:43.829
Did they sit and feel sorry for themselves?

01:24:43.829 --> 01:24:49.085
No, they acted, and they had a swag that was successful.

01:24:49.085 --> 01:25:00.400
After they got to the NFL, after they got to these places, they didn't still act like they did in college.

01:25:00.400 --> 01:25:06.657
They didn't act like they did in high school.

01:25:06.657 --> 01:25:09.874
You go from glory to glory.

01:25:20.000 --> 01:25:20.354
And the only way I can tell you all this, maybe, is to bring it to a natural level for you: sports.

01:25:36.710 --> 01:25:36.960
I love sports.

01:25:36.960 --> 01:25:41.371
But you go from glory to glory to glory to glory.

01:26:11.250 --> 01:26:11.560
And the way you are in the pros is not the way you're going to act when you were in high school.

01:26:11.560 --> 01:26:13.707
You've got to carry yourself differently.

01:26:13.707 --> 01:26:14.613
You're a victor.

01:26:14.613 --> 01:26:15.629
You're a champion.

01:26:15.629 --> 01:26:19.449
You've got to train like a champion.

01:26:19.449 --> 01:26:24.440
You've got to act like it.

01:26:25.580 --> 01:26:37.170
And I'm just trying to help stir you up so you don't have that victim mentality.

01:26:37.170 --> 01:27:29.200
Because if you have a victim mentality, you're never going to have a winner's mentality, and you're never going to be able to take over things and say, 'Listen, I've got the ring.

01:27:29.200 --> 01:27:45.727
' You know, like Pastor Chip; he has that old championship ring on his finger that he got from the Astros when he was a scout.

01:27:45.727 --> 01:27:48.560
It's a different mentality.

01:27:48.560 --> 01:27:55.240
So, I want to stretch you to believe bigger, to stretch yourself to think bigger.

01:27:55.240 --> 01:28:03.050
You've got to think bigger in these last days and not have that victim mentality.

01:28:03.860 --> 01:28:09.159
The Lord corrects me all the time because sometimes I feel sorry for myself.

01:28:09.159 --> 01:28:10.099
No, stop that!

01:28:10.099 --> 01:28:13.650
I've created you for more than that.

01:28:13.650 --> 01:28:17.520
Go back to the fundamentals.

01:28:17.520 --> 01:28:21.973
Go back to the basics of Christianity.

01:28:21.973 --> 01:28:27.040
Go back to when you're having a hard day.

01:28:27.040 --> 01:28:32.880
'How did you get here in the first place, Brandon?

01:28:32.880 --> 01:28:34.960
' Spending time with Me.

01:29:02.360 --> 01:29:02.713
That was all about the friendship sermon that I told you last time.

01:29:02.713 --> 01:29:06.053
Go back to the basics.

01:29:06.053 --> 01:29:17.436
Don't forget the fundamentals: reading your Bible, praying in the spirit, and fellowship with Me, singing songs.

01:29:17.436 --> 01:29:20.640
Go back to the ABCs.

01:29:20.640 --> 01:29:24.830
When you're a goose in the fog, it's like training in war.

01:29:38.280 --> 01:29:38.493
They repeat it until it's in that muscle memory.

01:29:38.920 --> 01:29:39.347
They just act.

01:29:48.314 --> 01:29:51.240
The moment something happens in war, they don't freeze because it's so grounded in them; it's just their muscle memory.

01:29:51.240 --> 01:29:55.820
Remember that doctor at the prayer conference?

01:29:55.820 --> 01:30:01.680
He said most wrecks always happen within a couple miles of the house because you're on autopilot.

01:30:03.360 --> 01:30:07.640
You don't think; you can just go there without even thinking.

01:30:11.914 --> 01:30:16.488
You don't even realize what street you're turning down a lot of times because you can be thinking about something else.

01:30:16.488 --> 01:30:30.509
And because you have muscle memory—you've done it so many times—your mind doesn't even have to really process within a couple miles of your house.

01:30:35.291 --> 01:30:43.011
You can just go there with your eyes closed, basically, because your mind already knows which way it's going to go before you even do it, because it's muscle memory.

01:30:43.011 --> 01:30:45.316
Just like that.

01:30:56.072 --> 01:30:56.504
That is grounded in you, and that's why we have to be with the word.

01:31:04.195 --> 01:31:04.430
It's just in us; you react immediately.

01:31:04.430 --> 01:31:08.740
What did you say about first response?

01:31:08.740 --> 01:31:14.400
What was your first response whenever he hurt his finger?

01:31:14.400 --> 01:31:23.390
When you do these things, what's your first response?

01:31:31.907 --> 01:31:32.293
The moment you come into trouble, what's your first response?

01:31:32.293 --> 01:31:36.240
Regardless of what you're going through, your first response matters.

01:31:36.240 --> 01:31:37.440
Your first response matters.

01:31:37.440 --> 01:31:44.080
It's not dropping a bad word or yelling at your kids, your wife, or your dog.

01:31:44.080 --> 01:31:46.140
What's your first response?

01:31:46.755 --> 01:31:46.960
The word.

01:31:46.960 --> 01:31:48.800
It's in you.

01:31:48.800 --> 01:31:49.387
It's muscle memory.

01:31:49.387 --> 01:31:52.187
What comes out of you out of the abundance of your heart?

01:32:02.240 --> 01:32:02.510
The mouth speaks.

01:32:02.510 --> 01:32:04.790
What's in abundance in your heart?

01:32:04.790 --> 01:32:08.370
Out of the abundance of your heart, the mouth speaks.

01:32:08.370 --> 01:32:10.429
What's your first response?

01:32:10.429 --> 01:32:14.909
If it's blankety-blank, if it's this or that, then you don't have enough muscle memory.

01:32:15.740 --> 01:32:24.160
You know, the word needs to become more of a priority in your life because of the abundance of your heart.

01:32:24.160 --> 01:32:25.385
